{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7cd37b93-7a0b-4def-9918-e40e8c3c642b","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support entirely.** That's the breaking change.\n\n### What happened\n\n- **MSTest.Sdk 3.3 and earlier** — defaulted to the **VSTest** runner (`vstest.console`).\n- **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** — switched the default to **Microsoft Testing Platform** but still allowed opting back into VSTest via `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`.\n- **MSTest.Sdk 4.x** — **removed VSTest support completely**. The `UseVSTest` property is no longer recognized, and the VSTest adapter is no longer bundled.\n\n### How to fix your CI\n\nReplace `vstest.console` with the built-in test host. The project itself becomes the test runner:\n\n```bash\n# Instead of:  vstest.console TestProject.dll\n# Use:\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n# Or run the compiled test executable directly:\ndotnet exec TestProject.dll\n```\n\nIf you use `dotnet test`, it already understands Microsoft Testing Platform for SDK-style projects. No other project changes are needed — your `.csproj` and test code are fine as-is.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1ed71c24-c412-468c-9976-5ba2f5c817fe","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, the default test runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft Testing Platform (the new runner). In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, VSTest support was completely removed.\n\nLet me explain this clearly.","outputTokens":370,"requestId":"9C43:18BE1:1967D17:1C5B2F6:69F86C6D"},"id":"3cdd5cff-1285-419b-a355-39db4f3463df","timestamp":"2026-05-04T09:52:59.268Z","parentId":"12e07e7b-283c-4276-b0ee-bfea7972563f"}
